The relationship between the magnificent Chicago Symphony Orchestra and Krannert Center that began in the Center&rsquo;s early years has only strengthened over time. Now, as one of the world&rsquo;s premier orchestras returns to one of the world&rsquo;s premier performance halls, David Afkham takes the podium for a program featuring Haydn&rsquo;s emotionally charged Mourning Symphony, Strauss&rsquo; radiant tone poem portraying a man&rsquo;s journey through death, and Brahms&rsquo; ethereal Symphony No. 3, a cornerstone of the symphonic repertoire that the Chicago Symphony Orchestra performed in its first season. Afkham, principal conductor of the Spanish National Orchestra and Chorus, is in high demand as a guest conductor with some of the world&rsquo;s finest orchestras and opera houses and is one of the most sought-after conductors to emerge from Germany in recent years.
&nbsp;
