The King&rsquo;s Singers were established in May 1968&mdash;one year before the doors of Krannert Center opened&mdash;by six recently graduated choral scholars from King&rsquo;s College, Cambridge, England. The world may have changed a lot in the 50 years since the original King&rsquo;s Singers came together, but today&rsquo;s group is still charged by the same driving force&mdash;to radiate every day the joy singing brings and to share that excitement with audiences through virtuosity and vision. The King&rsquo;s Singers&rsquo; musical craft, combined with their unique charm and their celebration of great music in all its diversity, has captured hearts worldwide&mdash;two Grammy Awards, an Emmy Award, and a place in Gramophone&rsquo;s Hall of Fame testify to that accomplishment. The ensemble&rsquo;s Krannert Center program, Finding Harmony, expresses the idea that singing is a language that can be spoken by anyone, and that uniting voices in harmony creates something greater and more beautiful than the sum of its parts. The a cappella performance will contain a delightful range of music, from medieval chant to pop hits, from newly commissioned works to jazz standards.





